content.text: Good, the `frpm` table has the relevant columns. Now let me query for the 10th-highest-enrollment school and compute its eligible free rate.

input.command: sqlite3 "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/california_schools.sqlite" "SELECT \"School Name\", \"Enrollment (K-12)\", \"Free Meal Count (K-12)\", \"Free Meal Count (K-12)\" / \"Enrollment (K-12)\" AS eligible_free_rate FROM frpm WHERE \"Enrollment (K-12)\" IS NOT NULL AND \"Enrollment (K-12)\" > 0 ORDER BY \"Enrollment (K-12)\" DESC LIMIT 15;"
input.description: Get top 15 schools by K-12 enrollment with free rate

input.command: sqlite3 "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/california_schools.sqlite" "SELECT \"Free Meal Count (K-12)\" * 1.0 / \"Enrollment (K-12)\" FROM frpm WHERE \"Enrollment (K-12)\" IS NOT NULL AND \"Enrollment (K-12)\" > 0 ORDER BY \"Enrollment (K-12)\" DESC LIMIT 1 OFFSET 9;"
